<h3 class="wiki-nav-item pb-2" id="connecting-to-daemon">
    It says it fails to connect to the daemon?
</h3>
<div class="ms-3">
    <p>
        This can be caused by a few different problems. Primarily, this will result from incorrectly following the <a href="/Wiki/Install/Windows">installation guide</a> on installation.<br/><br/>

        If you are sure that you have followed the installation guide correctly, or this issue just began occurring after an update to OTD, then it is likely that you have
        broken settings or outdated plugins installed. You can remedy this with the below.
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>Press <kbd>Win</kbd> + <kbd>R</kbd> and type in <code>%localappdata%\OpenTabletDriver</code></li>
        <li>Delete or move the <code>settings.json</code> file from inside this folder.</li>
        <li>If this persists after also remove the <code>Plugins</code> folder.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
        If you have a <code>userdata</code> folder next to the binaries of OpenTabletDriver, you will need to remove the files above from that folder instead.<br><br>

        If you still can't get it working after the solutions above please join our <a href="/Discord">Discord</a>.
        It might be a completely different issue!
    </p>
</div>

